72 /*========== Static Function Prototypes =====================================*/
73 /** get a boolean for if any timing error (current or recorded) occurred */
74 static bool CANTX_AnySysMonTimingIssueDetected(const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim);
75 
76 /*========== Static Function Implementations ================================*/
77 static bool CANTX_AnySysMonTimingIssueDetected(const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
78  FAS_ASSERT(kpkCanShim != NULL_PTR);
79  SYSM_TIMING_VIOLATION_RESPONSE_s recordedTimingViolations = {0};
80  SYSM_GetRecordedTimingViolations(&recordedTimingViolations);
81 
82  const bool anyTimingViolation =
83  (recordedTimingViolations.recordedViolationAny ||
84  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->taskEngineTimingViolationError ||
85  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task1msTimingViolationError ||
86  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task10msTimingViolationError ||
87  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task100msTimingViolationError ||
88  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task100msAlgoTimingViolationError);
89 
90  return anyTimingViolation;
91 }

93 /*========== Extern Function Implementations ================================*/
94 extern uint32_t CANTX_BmsState(
95  CAN_MESSAGE_PROPERTIES_s message,
96  uint8_t *pCanData,
97  uint8_t *pMuxId,
98  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
99  FAS_ASSERT(message.id == CANTX_BMS_STATE_ID);
100  FAS_ASSERT(message.dlc == CAN_FOXBMS_MESSAGES_DEFAULT_DLC);
101  FAS_ASSERT(pCanData != NULL_PTR);
102  FAS_ASSERT(pMuxId == NULL_PTR); /* pMuxId is not used here, therefore has to be NULL_PTR */
103  FAS_ASSERT(kpkCanShim != NULL_PTR);
104  uint64_t messageData = 0u;
105 
106  DATA_READ_DATA(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState, kpkCanShim->pTableInsulation, kpkCanShim->pTableMsl);
107 
108  /* AXIVION Disable Style Generic-NoMagicNumbers: Signal data defined in .dbc file. */
109  /* State */
110  uint64_t data = (uint64_t)BMS_GetState();
111  /* set data in CAN frame */
112  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 0u, 4u, data, message.endianness);
113 
114  /* Connected strings */
115  data = (uint64_t)BMS_GetNumberOfConnectedStrings();
116 
117  /* set data in CAN frame */
118  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 4u, 4u, data, message.endianness);
119 
120  /* General warning: TODO */
121 
122  /* General error - implement now */
123  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(DIAG_IsAnyFatalErrorSet());
124  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 10u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
125 
126  /* Emergency shutoff */
127  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(BMS_IsTransitionToErrorStateActive());
128  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 11u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
129 
130  /* Number of deactivated strings: TODO */
131 
132  /* sys mon error */
133  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(CANTX_AnySysMonTimingIssueDetected(kpkCanShim));
134  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 12u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
135 
136  /* Insulation monitoring active */
137  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableInsulation->isImdRunning);
138  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 13u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
139 
140  /* Error: insulation */
141  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->criticalLowInsulationResistanceError);
142  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 23u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
143 
144  /* Insulation resistance */
145  float_t signalData = (float_t)kpkCanShim->pTableInsulation->insulationResistance_kOhm;
146  signalData = signalData * 0.1f; /* convert kOhm to 10kOhm */
147  data = (uint64_t)signalData;
148  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 56u, 8u, data, message.endianness);
149 
150  /* Charging complete: TODO */
151 
152  /* Heater state: TODO */
153  /* Cooling state: TODO */
154 
155  /* Error: Precharge voltage */
156  data = 0u; /* No precharge error detected */
157  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
158  if (kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->prechargeAbortedDueToVoltage[s] == true) {
159  data = 1u;
160  }
161  }
162  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 16u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
163 
164  /* Error: Precharge current */
165  data = 0u; /* No precharge error detected */
166  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
167  if (kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->prechargeAbortedDueToCurrent[s] == true) {
168  data = 1u;
169  }
170  }
171  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 17u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
172 
173  /* Error: MCU die temperature */
174  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->mcuDieTemperatureViolationError);
175  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 18u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
176 
177  /* Error: master overtemperature: TODO */
178  /* Error: master undertemperature: TODO */
179 
180  /* Main fuse state */
181  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->mainFuseError);
182  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 21u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
183 
184  /* Error: interlock */
185  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->interlockOpenedError);
186  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 22u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
187 
188  /* Error: Can timing */
189  data = kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->stateRequestTimingViolationError;
190  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 24u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
191 
192  /* Error: Overcurrent pack charge */
193  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->packChargeOvercurrent;
194  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 25u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
195 
196  /* Error: Overcurrent pack discharge */
197  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->packDischargeOvercurrent;
198  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 26u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
199 
200  /* Error: Alert flag */
201  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->alertFlagSetError);
202  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 27u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
203 
204  /* Error: NVRAM CRC */
205  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->framReadCrcError);
206  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 28u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
207  /* AXIVION Enable Style Generic-NoMagicNumbers: */
208 
209  /* now copy data in the buffer that will be use to send data */
210  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(messageData, pCanData, message.endianness);
211 
212  return 0;
213 }

215 extern uint32_t CANTX_BmsStateDetails(
216  CAN_MESSAGE_PROPERTIES_s message,
217  uint8_t *pCanData,
218  uint8_t *pMuxId,
219  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
220  FAS_ASSERT(message.id == CANTX_BMS_STATE_DETAILS_ID);
221  FAS_ASSERT(message.idType == CANTX_BMS_STATE_DETAILS_ID_TYPE);
222  FAS_ASSERT(message.dlc == CAN_FOXBMS_MESSAGES_DEFAULT_DLC);
223  FAS_ASSERT(pCanData != NULL_PTR);
224  FAS_ASSERT(pMuxId == NULL_PTR); /* pMuxId is not used here, therefore has to be NULL_PTR */
225  FAS_ASSERT(kpkCanShim != NULL_PTR);
226  uint64_t messageData = 0u;
227 
228  DATA_READ_DATA(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState);
229  SYSM_TIMING_VIOLATION_RESPONSE_s recordedTimingViolations = {0};
230  SYSM_GetRecordedTimingViolations(&recordedTimingViolations);
231 
232  /* AXIVION Disable Style Generic-NoMagicNumbers: Signal data defined in .dbc file. */
233  /* current violation engine */
234  uint64_t data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->taskEngineTimingViolationError);
235  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 0u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
236  /* current violation 1ms */
237  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task1msTimingViolationError);
238  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 1u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
239  /* current violation 10ms */
240  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task10msTimingViolationError);
241  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 2u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
242  /* current violation 100ms */
243  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task100msTimingViolationError);
244  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 3u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
245  /* current violation 100ms algorithm */
246  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->task100msAlgoTimingViolationError);
247  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 4u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
248 
249  /* recorded violation engine */
250  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(recordedTimingViolations.recordedViolationEngine);
251  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 8u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
252  /* recorded violation 1ms */
253  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(recordedTimingViolations.recordedViolation1ms);
254  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 9u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
255  /* recorded violation 10ms */
256  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(recordedTimingViolations.recordedViolation10ms);
257  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 10u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
258  /* recorded violation 100ms */
259  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(recordedTimingViolations.recordedViolation100ms);
260  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 11u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
261  /* recorded violation 100ms algorithm */
262  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(recordedTimingViolations.recordedViolation100msAlgo);
263  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 12u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
264  /* AXIVION Enable Style Generic-NoMagicNumbers: */
265 
266  /* now copy data in the buffer that will be use to send data */
267  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(messageData, pCanData, message.endianness);
268 
269  return 0;
270 }

272 extern uint32_t CANTX_StringState(
273  CAN_MESSAGE_PROPERTIES_s message,
274  uint8_t *pCanData,
275  uint8_t *pMuxId,
276  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
277  FAS_ASSERT(message.id == CANTX_STRING_STATE_ID);
278  FAS_ASSERT(message.idType == CANTX_STRING_STATE_ID_TYPE);
279  FAS_ASSERT(message.dlc == CAN_FOXBMS_MESSAGES_DEFAULT_DLC);
280  FAS_ASSERT(pCanData != NULL_PTR);
281  FAS_ASSERT(pMuxId != NULL_PTR);
282  FAS_ASSERT(*pMuxId < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS);
283  FAS_ASSERT(kpkCanShim != NULL_PTR);
284  uint64_t messageData = 0u;
285  uint64_t data = 0;
286 
287  const uint8_t stringNumber = *pMuxId;
288 
289  /* First signal to transmit cell voltages: get database values */
290  if (stringNumber == 0u) {
291  /* Do not read pTableMsl and pTableErrorState as they already are read
292  * with a higher frequency from CAN_TxState callback */
293  DATA_READ_DATA(kpkCanShim->pTableRsl, kpkCanShim->pTableMol);
294  }
295 
296  /* AXIVION Disable Style Generic-NoMagicNumbers: Signal data defined in .dbc file. */
297  /* mux value */
298  data = (uint64_t)stringNumber;
299  /* set data in CAN frame */
300  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 0u, 4u, data, message.endianness);
301 
302  /* String connected */
303  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(BMS_IsStringClosed(stringNumber));
304  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 4u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
305 
306  /* Balancing active: TODO */
307 
308  /* String fuse blown */
309  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->stringFuseError[stringNumber]);
310  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 6u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
311 
312  /* Error: Deep-discharge */
313  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->deepDischargeDetectedError[stringNumber]);
314  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 7u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
315 
316  /* Error: Overtemperature charge */
317  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->overtemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
318  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 8u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
319 
320  /* Error: Undertemperature charge */
321  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->undertemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
322  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 9u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
323 
324  /* Error: Overtemperature discharge */
325  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->overtemperatureDischarge[stringNumber];
326  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 10u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
327 
328  /* Error: Undertemperature discharge */
329  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->undertemperatureDischarge[stringNumber];
330  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 11u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
331 
332  /* Error: Overcurrent charge */
333  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->cellChargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u) ||
334  (kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->stringChargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u)) {
335  data = 1u;
336  } else {
337  data = 0u;
338  }
339  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 12u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
340 
341  /* Error: Overcurrent discharge */
342  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->cellDischargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u) ||
343  (kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->stringDischargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u)) {
344  data = 1u;
345  } else {
346  data = 0u;
347  }
348  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 13u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
349 
350  /* Error: Overvoltage */
351  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->overVoltage[stringNumber];
352  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 14u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
353 
354  /* Error: Undervoltage */
355  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMsl->underVoltage[stringNumber];
356  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 15u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
357 
358  /* Info: Overtemperature charge - MOL */
359  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMol->overtemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
360  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 16u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
361 
362  /* Info: Undertemperature charge - MOL */
363  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMol->undertemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
364  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 17u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
365 
366  /* Info: Overtemperature discharge - MOL */
367  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMol->overtemperatureDischarge[stringNumber];
368  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 18u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
369 
370  /* Info: Undertemperature discharge - MOL */
371  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMol->undertemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
372  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 19u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
373 
374  /* Info: Overcurrent charge - MOL */
375  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableMol->cellChargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u) ||
376  (kpkCanShim->pTableMol->stringChargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u)) {
377  data = 1u;
378  } else {
379  data = 0u;
380  }
381  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 20u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
382 
383  /* Info: Overcurrent discharge - MOL */
384  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableMol->cellDischargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u) ||
385  (kpkCanShim->pTableMol->stringDischargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u)) {
386  data = 1u;
387  } else {
388  data = 0u;
389  }
390  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 21u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
391 
392  /* Info: Overvoltage - MOL */
393  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMol->overVoltage[stringNumber];
394  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 22u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
395 
396  /* Info: Undervoltage - MOL */
397  data = kpkCanShim->pTableMol->underVoltage[stringNumber];
398  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 23u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
399 
400  /* Warning: Overtemperature charge - RSL */
401  data = kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->overtemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
402  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 24u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
403 
404  /* Warning: Undertemperature charge - RSL */
405  data = kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->undertemperatureCharge[stringNumber];
406  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 25u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
407 
408  /* Warning: Overtemperature discharge - RSL */
409  data = kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->overtemperatureDischarge[stringNumber];
410  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 26u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
411 
412  /* Warning: Undertemperature discharge - RSL */
413  data = kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->undertemperatureDischarge[stringNumber];
414  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 27u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
415 
416  /* Warning: Overcurrent charge - RSL */
417  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->cellChargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u) ||
418  (kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->stringChargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u)) {
419  data = 1u;
420  } else {
421  data = 0u;
422  }
423  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 28u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
424 
425  /* Warning: Overcurrent discharge - RSL */
426  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableMol->cellDischargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u) ||
427  (kpkCanShim->pTableMol->stringDischargeOvercurrent[stringNumber] == 1u)) {
428  data = 1u;
429  } else {
430  data = 0u;
431  }
432  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 29u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
433 
434  /* Warning: Overvoltage - RSL */
435  data = kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->overVoltage[stringNumber];
436  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 30u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
437 
438  /* Warning: Undervoltage - RSL */
439  data = kpkCanShim->pTableRsl->underVoltage[stringNumber];
440  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 31u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
441 
442  /* Error: Positive string contactor */
443  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(
444  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->contactorInPositivePathOfStringFeedbackError[stringNumber]);
445  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 32u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
446 
447  /* Error: Negative string contactor */
448  data = CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(
449  kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->contactorInNegativePathOfStringFeedbackError[stringNumber]);
450  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 33u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
451 
452  /* Error: Slave hardware: TODO */
453 
454  /* Error: Daisy-chain base: communication */
455  data = kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->afeCommunicationSpiError[stringNumber];
456  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 35u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
457 
458  /* Error: Daisy-chain redundancy: communication: TODO */
459  /* Error: Daisy-chain base: CRC */
460  data = kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->afeCommunicationCrcError[stringNumber];
461  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 37u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
462 
463  /* Error: Daisy-chain redundancy: CRC: TODO */
464  /* Error: Daisy-chain base: Voltage out of operating range */
465  data = kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->afeCellVoltageInvalidError[stringNumber];
466  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 39u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
467 
468  /* Error: Daisy-chain redundancy: Voltage out of operating range: TODO */
469  /* Error: Daisy-chain base: Temperature out of operating range */
470  data = kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->afeCellTemperatureInvalidError[stringNumber];
471  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 41u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
472 
473  /* Error: Daisy-chain redundancy: Voltage out of operating range: TODO */
474 
475  /* Error: current measurement */
476  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->currentMeasurementInvalidError[stringNumber] == true) ||
477  (kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->currentMeasurementTimeoutError[stringNumber] == true)) {
478  data = 1u;
479  } else {
480  data = 0u;
481  }
482  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 43u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
483 
484  /* Error: Coulomb counting measurement */
485  data = kpkCanShim->pTableErrorState->currentSensorCoulombCounterTimeoutError[stringNumber];
486  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&messageData, 44u, 1u, data, message.endianness);
487 
488  /* Error: Energy counting measurement */

527  /* AXIVION Enable Style Generic-NoMagicNumbers: */
528 
529  /* Open wire number: TODO */
530 
531  /* now copy data in the buffer that will be used to send data */
532  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(messageData, pCanData, message.endianness);
533 
534  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
535  (*pMuxId)++;
536 
537  /* Check mux value */
538  if (*pMuxId >= BS_NR_OF_STRINGS) {
539  *pMuxId = 0u;
540  }
